editorialSummary.text: Cozy, elegant bistro specializing in Mediterranean-inspired seafood, steak & vegetarian bowls.

originalText.text: Very Busy on Saturday Night. Despite the crowd we had a pleasant greeting by the manager/owner(?) and timely service by our waiter. The food was filling and tasty, and the drinks were small, But Strong!  If you're looking for a busy  atmosphere, this will work well for you.

originalText.text: Great experience. Delicious food and drinks. I celebrated my birthday, and they gave us a few drinks and dessert at the house. Service was fast and efficient. The quantities were decent, and the food was delicious. We would go back to try other items on the menu.

originalText.text: Such a strange experience. They advertise a bottomless brunch but they don’t actually have a bottomless brunch. The manager was rude to his staff in front of us which made us feel uncomfortable. The food portions are small and the food is not very good. I do not recommend this place - avoid it like the plague- unless you enjoy being overcharged and a part of weird encounters.

i’m waiting to see how my nightmare is handled. There is just too much to say about all the disappointments and un edible. Fish
branzino that was dry, metallic tasting and tasteless in some weird tastless sauce
after having been disappointed with the sandwich, I ordered because there was nothing inside. It was like a tiny sloppy Joe inside but mostly bread and very salty. When I said, put the sauce on the side they do
it was mostly sauce, no meat horrible. He convinced me to order something else cause he ran out of he said. The short ribs sandwich meat. I guess that’s why it was all sauce and shreds of minuscule meat. It’s come to the point where the quality of food in a lot of restaurants has gone down. The prices have gone up and it’s not worth eating out anymore. most places I get better fish and citerella, I know it’s fresh. It taste delicious just plain. The texture is soft, flaky, wonderful fresh fish. It took him an hour to have this brought over from a few blocks away when fish takes only about five minutes to cook. I knew it was frozen as I grew up in sheep,sheaf bay and always got fish from the docks there since I was knee-high to a grasshopper. I know fresh fish. At compromises 90% of my protein as I’m not supposed to have meat./
Only go to places that are consistent and good and know there’s some quality to the food and how it’s prepared. It’s a shame Ruined my dinner. I had the dessert which was excellent the tiramisu. I’m sure that’s brought in from outside but it is very good better than a lot of places. It it
So there I was with dessert for dinner. I have more to say, but I’m stopping now to see if I ever get a receipt that shows the amount I paid on my credit card I got A copy of what I ordered instead of a credit card receipt that shows what I paid was charged and the tip. I never got receipts like that from restaurants I got normal credit card receipts there was no amount nothing I asked for one receipt and then I asked for a credit, and I got neither, no more business here from me. It’s a quaint, charming place but we want good food when we’re paying for it. I can eat better at home. My cooking is good!. It’s just times I don’t feel like cooking. Not that broiling or sautéing a piece of fish, is cooking and steaming a vegetable . But I have health issues and I’m tired often. Wish I could’ve done more business with this place but I have to be able to eat the food and not be ripped off with it empty almost that looks like sloppy Joe from Subway decades ago! When I had this sandwich a few times before it was edible not a lot of meat but it was OK , I don’t know what the hell he did and if it’s true, he probably ran out of product and gave me nothing inside virtually. I said no sauce it was all sauce 75%. I would’ve liked to write up a nice write up. I hate writing negative things about places, but he he pushed me to order again , I couldn’t eat the fish that as I stated. I hope they get their act together. hopefully there are other dishes that are better there. But I’m not willing to try anymore. This left a very bad taste in my mouth. double entendre
I wish them well like I said, I hope they get it together.

originalText.text: I really loved the place, atmosphere was amazing, music is so good there. Service was outstanding, in the end of our meal we got complementary dessert. I wasn’t crazy about the food. Pasta wasn’t good, we asked aldente, but it def wasn’t, and tasted like they just got this pasta from the corner store .We also ordered fish and it was pretty dry, and tasteless, onion soup was very salty. For this quantity of food price was very high. 15$ for tiny soup it’s too much . 15$ for salad was ok, but size of the salad was really small. Maybe next time I will try something else and will be more impressed.
